<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-2196] camel-cxf - CxfProducer in POJO mode should be able to use POJO object directly without wrapped as List</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-2196</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See camel-example-cxf-async&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the client code that sends to the server using CxfProducer. I have to wrap my POJO in a List object.&lt;br/&gt;
CxfProducer should be smarter and be able to do this itself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It can do this by converting the payload to an iterator and use that to construct the list.&lt;br/&gt;
Then it works for POJO objects directly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
